# Architecture Rules

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── common/              # Shared utilities, decorators, guards, interceptors
│   ├── decorators/
│   ├── guards/
│   ├── interceptors/
│   ├── filters/
│   ├── pipes/
│   └── utils/
├── config/              # Configuration (database, jwt, upload, etc.)
├── modules/
│   ├── auth/            # Authentication & authorization
│   ├── users/           # Users
│   ├── requests/        # Service requests
│   ├── proposals/       # Proposals
│   ├── reviews/         # Reviews
│   ├── messages/        # Messages & chat
│   ├── discussions/     # Public comments
│   ├── blog/            # Blog
│   ├── reports/         # Reports
│   ├── achievements/    # Gamification
│   ├── notifications/   # Notifications
│   ├── upload/          # File upload
│   └── admin/           # Admin panel
├── database/
│   ├── entities/        # TypeORM entities
│   ├── migrations/      # Database migrations
│   └── seeds/           # Seed data
└── main.ts
```

## Module Structure

Each module should follow this structure:
```
modules/module-name/
├── module-name.controller.ts  # HTTP request handling
├── module-name.service.ts     # Business logic
├── module-name.module.ts      # Module configuration
├── dto/                       # Data Transfer Objects
│   ├── create-module-name.dto.ts
│   ├── update-module-name.dto.ts
│   └── get-module-name.dto.ts
├── module-name.controller.spec.ts  # Unit tests
└── module-name.service.spec.ts    # Unit tests
```

## Module Principles

1. **One module = one business entity/functionality**
2. **Dependencies between modules through imports in *.module.ts**
3. **Controllers only for HTTP requests, no business logic**
4. **Services contain all business logic**
5. **Use dependency injection for all dependencies**

## Common Layer

The `common/` directory contains:
- **Decorators**: Custom parameter decorators (e.g., `@CurrentUser()`)
- **Guards**: Authentication and authorization guards
- **Interceptors**: Response transformation, logging
- **Filters**: Exception filters for error handling
- **Pipes**: Custom validation pipes
- **Utils**: Shared utility functions
